HEADWORD: Alto-stratus
<hw>Al`to-stra"tus</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>altus</ets> high + L. & E.
<ets>stratus</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Meteor.)</fld> <def>A cloud formation
similar to cirro-stratus, but heavier and at a lower level; a stratus
cloud at an intermediate altitude of 2 or 3 miles.</def>⟦br⟧
